      <title></title>
      <link>/docs/blackbox/mac/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>/docs/blackbox/mac/</guid>
      <description>

&lt;h1 id=&#34;install-on-mac-osx:d680e8a854a7cbad6d490c445cba2eba&#34;&gt;Install On Mac OSX&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;step-1-install-docker:d680e8a854a7cbad6d490c445cba2eba&#34;&gt;Step 1: Install Docker&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1Album Blackbox is distributed as a Docker Image.  You must have Docker installed on your system to use it. Click &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.docker.com/products/docker-toolbox&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt; here to download Docker Toolbox &lt;i class=&#34;fa fa-download&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  Please reference &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.docker.com/mac/step_one/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Docker Toolbox installation guide&lt;/a&gt; for installation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After installation, click the Kitematic icon to start Docker:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;../img/docs/mac/kitematic.png&#34; class=&#34;screenshot&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A login page shows up.  Login is optional, you can just click the &lt;code&gt;SKIP FOR NOW&lt;/code&gt; button:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;../img/docs/mac/kitematic_login.png&#34; class=&#34;screenshot&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After the login page, Kitematic home page shows up:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;../img/docs/mac/kitematic_home.png&#34; class=&#34;screenshot&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;step-2-install-blackbox:d680e8a854a7cbad6d490c445cba2eba&#34;&gt;Step 2: Install Blackbox&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Enter &lt;code&gt;1album&lt;/code&gt; in the search box to search for 1Album Blackbox, then click the &lt;code&gt;CREATE&lt;/code&gt; button to download and install it:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;../img/docs/mac/search_1album_blackbox.png&#34; class=&#34;screenshot&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Downloading:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;../img/docs/mac/downloading_1album_blackbox.png&#34; class=&#34;screenshot&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After download is completed, this error message shows up.  Don&amp;rsquo;t worry, this is because we haven&amp;rsquo;t setup &lt;code&gt;/data&lt;/code&gt; volume yet.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;../img/docs/mac/1album_blackbox_first_boot.png&#34; class=&#34;screenshot&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;step-3-setup-data-volunme:d680e8a854a7cbad6d490c445cba2eba&#34;&gt;Step 3: Setup Data Volunme&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1Album Blackbox stores everything in &lt;code&gt;/data&lt;/code&gt; volume. You must associate it to a local folder before starting the blackbox. Open Seetings -&amp;gt; Volumes page, then click the &lt;code&gt;CHANGE&lt;/code&gt; button corresponding to the &lt;code&gt;/data&lt;/code&gt; volume:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;../img/docs/mac/volume_settings.png&#34; class=&#34;screenshot&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Select any folder you want. Note that you must not manually alter the content in this folder, otherwise your data inside the blackbox may be damaged or lost.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;../img/docs/mac/select_folder.png&#34; class=&#34;screenshot&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After a folder is selected, it is listed next to the &lt;code&gt;/data&lt;/code&gt; volume:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;../img/docs/mac/data_linked.png&#34; class=&#34;screenshot&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Besides &lt;code&gt;/data&lt;/code&gt;, there are three optional volumes that can be configured.  &lt;code&gt;/export&lt;/code&gt; is for exporting data out of the blackbox, and &lt;code&gt;/import&lt;/code&gt; is for importing data back in. &lt;code&gt;/cache&lt;/code&gt; is for storing temporarily files such as thumbnail images.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;../img/docs/mac/other_volumes.png&#34; class=&#34;screenshot&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Click &lt;code&gt;HOME&lt;/code&gt; when you&amp;rsquo;re done.  The blackbox is now started:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;../img/docs/mac/1album_blackbox_home.png&#34; class=&#34;screenshot&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;step-4-link-account:d680e8a854a7cbad6d490c445cba2eba&#34;&gt;Step 4: Link Account&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You must add the blackbox to your account to start using it.  First, write down the &lt;code&gt;Device Key&lt;/code&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;../img/docs/mac/1album_blackbox_device_key.png&#34; class=&#34;screenshot&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then open 1Album app and enter the &lt;code&gt;Device Key&lt;/code&gt; as below:&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;div class=&#34;iphone6&#34;&gt;
   &lt;div class=&#34;iphone6-screen&#34;&gt;
       &lt;img src=&#34;../img/docs/add_blackbox_en.gif&#34;&gt;
   &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Now this blackbox will work for you.  Your account name is listed on the blackbox console:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;../img/docs/mac/1album_blackbox_login.png&#34; class=&#34;screenshot&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
